ithin walking distance from <strong>Monastiraki</strong> and<strong> Ancient Agora, Psyri</strong> and <strong>Kerameikos</strong>, as well as the iconic Acropolis with its modern museum, Nema captures the true spirit of the city, along with its vibrant identity. You are welcome to discover the authenticity of <strong>Central Municipal Athens Market</strong> with thousands of colors and aromas bursting all around.</p>\n<p>As its name dictates (<strong>Nema stands for yarn in Greek</strong>), the building is an irreplaceable part of the whole area’s history that has been distinguished by a rich textile industry. You can still feel its presence as you are walking up and down the narrow-cobbled streets, mingling with the locals, discovering hidden treasures of culture and entertainment. After all, <strong>Athens is a city that never sleeps</strong> with an abundance of bars, restaurants and quaint taverns, night clubs and parties. Delve in <strong>Greek gastronomy</strong> at its finest and indulge in wine tasting experiences, tours and visits to both historic and contemporary wonders.</p>\n","css":{"element":"div","class":"animation--up","color":"primary-dark"}}]}]},"4":{"wrapper":{"fluid":true,"css":{"border":"0","backgroundColor":"#FFFFFF"},"rows":[{"css":{"padding":"80px 0 0 0","border":"0"},"columns":{"sizes":["col-md-12 animation--up"]}}]},"rows":[{"columns":[{"mapSettings":{"lat":37.9790403,"lng":23.725242,"center":[37.9790403,23.725242],"zoom":12},"mapStyle":{"height":"500px"},"css":{"element":"div","class":"animation--up","color":"primary-dark"}}]}]},"5":{"wrapper":{"fluid":true,"css":{"border":"0","backgroundColor":"#04456D"},"rows":[{"css":{"padding":"80px 0 60px 0","border":"0","maxWidth":"1440px","margin":"0 auto"},"columns":{"sizes":["col-md-12  animation--up"]}}]},"rows":[{"columns":[{"text":"MORE HOTELS","link":{"pathname":"/dreams-luxury-suites","api":"/pages/room/room1"},"css":{"element":"div","class":"title-case-primary text-uppercase text-center ani